# Path prefixes exempt from the check-typography action.
#
# The original rationale (staying byte-identical to upstream
# whg517/browser-bridge for clean merges) ended with the rebrand to
# chromium-bridge (ADR-0023). This list only holds files that deliberately
# carry banned look-alike/fullwidth punctuation, by EXACT path so nothing else
# rides along, and it must only ever shrink:
# - zh locale bundles (extension .yml, desktop .ts): fullwidth CJK punctuation
#   and curly quotes are correct Chinese typography. Only zh_CN.ts is listed
#   for the desktop app; zh_TW.ts uses only CJK marks the checker already
#   allows, and en.* files are pure ASCII.
# - Translated docs (*.zh_CN.md / *.zh_TW.md): legitimate CJK punctuation,
#   exempted per exact path. English docs are NOT exempt - they are plain ASCII.
#
# Whole-script CJK containment (an untranslated Chinese label leaking into an
# English surface) is policed separately by scripts/check-cjk.ts, not here.
# Non-banned functional glyphs (U+2022 masking bullet, U+2192, U+26A0, U+2260)
# are not look-alikes and need no exemption.
src/apps/extension/src/locales/zh_CN.yml
src/apps/extension/src/locales/zh_TW.yml
src/apps/desktop/ui/src/locales/zh_CN.ts
README.zh_CN.md
README.zh_TW.md
docs/quickstart.zh_CN.md
docs/quickstart.zh_TW.md
docs/privacy-policy.zh_CN.md
docs/privacy-policy.zh_TW.md
